{# Agent task: apply requested changes to an existing skill. #}
# Modify existing skill

Change request: `{{ upstream['gather-update'].task_path }}`
(`{name, namespace, path, description}`). Skill on disk at
`path` — `fs_read` SKILL.md and any `references/` or
`scripts/` files needed to understand the change.

## Task

Apply the user's `description` request. Stay strictly within
scope — modify only what the request covers. Preserve
existing functionality unless explicitly asked to remove it.

Structural changes (new sections, new files, removed files)
are fine when the request requires them; otherwise edit text
in place.

## Output

Construct `output.yaml` (matching `schemas/files.yaml`) via
loom's schema-driven writer.

```bash
LOOM=~/.kiro/skills/home/loom/scripts/loom.sh
WD={{ run.workdir }}

$LOOM output init "$WD" --task modify-changes

$LOOM output add "$WD" --task modify-changes \
    --set 'files[].path=/abs/path/to/edited.md' \
    --set 'files[-1].action=modified' \
    --set 'files[].path=/abs/path/to/new-section.md' \
    --set 'files[-1].action=created'
```

Syntax: `[]` appends, `[-1]` targets the last appended entry.
